
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `apt-key` baraye modiriat kelid-haye GPG baraye `apt` (Advanced Package Tool) estefade mishavad. In kelid-ha baraye sanjesh dorosti package-ha az manabe motabar (repositories) estefade mishavand. Dar vaghe, `apt-key` komak mikonad ke system shoma motmaen shavad ke package-haye download shode aslan taghir nakarde and va az yek manbae emtebar darand.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `apt-key add <file>`  --> 🔑 Ezafe kardane kelid jadid az yek file.
    🔹 `apt-key del <keyid>` --> 🗑️ Hazf kardane yek kelid ba estefade az ID aan.
    🔹 `apt-key list`        --> 📜 Namayesh listi az hameye kelid-haye mojood.
    🔹 `apt-key export <keyid>` --> 📤 Kharooj dadane kelid ba ID moshakhas be soorate ASCII.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ apt-key add google.gpg
    
    🔹 Ezafe kardane kelide google.gpg baraye repository google.

    $ apt-key list
    
    🔹 Namayesh listi az hameye kelid-ha, ID aanha va etela'at digar.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ apt-key del 82B1299274294E3E
    
    🔹 Hazf kelidi ba ID `82B1299274294E3E` (agar in ID dar system shoma bashad). Bayad ba etminan kelidi ra hazf konid, chon hazf kelid-ha mohem ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `apt-key` command is used to manage GPG keys for `apt` (Advanced Package Tool). These keys are used to authenticate packages from trusted repositories. In essence, `apt-key` helps ensure that your system only installs packages that have not been tampered with and come from a legitimate source.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `apt-key add <file>`  --> 🔑 Add a new key from a file.
    🔹 `apt-key del <keyid>` --> 🗑️ Delete a key using its ID.
    🔹 `apt-key list`        --> 📜 Display a list of all available keys.
    🔹 `apt-key export <keyid>` --> 📤 Export a key with a specific ID in ASCII format.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ apt-key add google.gpg
    
    🔹 Adds the google.gpg key for the Google repository.

    $ apt-key list
    
    🔹 Displays a list of all keys, their IDs, and other information.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ apt-key del 82B1299274294E3E
    
    🔹 Deletes the key with ID `82B1299274294E3E` (if this ID exists on your system). Be careful when deleting keys, as key management is crucial.
